  "text": "The variables countPanI AA , countPanI AB , and countPanI BB are the sums of the genotypes for a specific sample from the catches, and a, b, and c are the probabilities for each of the three PanI genotypes of belonging to the NEAC group. This enabled us to calculate the Pearson correlation coefficient between the estimates from Equations (1) and (2). To test the level of differentiation between locally assigned NEAC and NCC, we made an F ST test based on [CITATION_1] h estimator for both LG1 and the total dataset.",
